Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Rare opportunity to buy a 15,200 sq. ft. industrial building in East St. Catharines. Located blocks from QEW highway access and commercial amenities. This building is equipped with a loading dock, gradelevel door, 12 ft. clear height, finished offices, paved on-site parking, and a small data centre. Industrial buildings for sale are a rare find in this market so act quickly. The building is currently finished over 50% office space which can be good for a buyer who needs that, or the offices can be demolished for industrial uses.

Industrial property for sale in St. Catharines with two buildings on site of similar size, totaling approximately 20,000 sq. ft. on 4.10 acres. This unique opportunity could entertain buyers that want both buildings for themselves or one to occupy and one to lease out for investment. The extra acreage could allow for future expansion should a buyer want to develop more than what is currently there. The buildings are equipped with 14 ft. clear height, 3 phase power, loading docks, and grade level door access. This could be an ideal opportunity for ACMPR medical cannabis growers, especially ones with multiple licenses but it can also be used for warehouse, manufacturing, and service uses. The location is close to the QEW for highway access and is close to commercial amenities. Seller wishes to maintain privacy so please do not visit the property without making arrangements first.

Here's your opportunity to own an industrial investment property with highway exposure in the heart of St. Catharines with visibility from theQEW. With St. Catharines being the business hub of the Niagara region this building is well situated with nearby commercial amenities, exposure, and highway access. This building currently has two tenants consisting of a vehicle collision repair centre and a stair maker, and there is plenty of potential upside in rent.
